** Hello, Hej, ** ** 你好 ** ** , Salut! **

At ** Flight Centre Travel Group (FCTG) ** our purpose is to 'open up the
world for those who want to see'. Every day, we give people all around the
world the opportunity to experience something amazing – travel!

As a forward-thinking Machine Learning Scientist, you will support the Leader
of AI/ML, in development and implementation of cutting-edge data science and
machine learning experiments within our organisation.

This role involves developing and deploying scalable ML models, creating
innovative ML pipelines, and extracting actionable insights from complex
datasets to drive strategic decisions and technological advancements. As the
Machine Learning Scientist you'll be at the forefront of exploring and  
integrating foundation models and novel ML techniques.

If you'd like to contribute significantly to our mission of delivering
impactful, technologically advanced solutions to complex problems in diverse
domains, please apply!

** Day to day: **

  * Design and implement data science and ML experiments, setting appropriate metrics, benchmarks, milestones, and effectively communicating results 
  * Construct and iterate on ML pipelines to provide scalable insights 
  * Create tools for data analysis and visualisation 
  * Manipulate large, complex datasets, applying innovative feature engineering techniques. 
  * Optimise model performance through fine-tuning 
  * Develop novel evaluation and benchmarking methods including QAs 
  * Deploy large-scale machine learning models in production environments 
  * Enhance the safety, security, and integrity of our AI system architectures, contributing to the platform’s success and reliability 
  * Promote ethical AI principles across all projects, ensuring fairness, transparency, and accountability 
  * Collaborate with cross-disciplinary teams to uncover new applications for ML solutions across the organisation 

** Experience required: **

  * At least 5 years of commercial development experience in ML and data science, with a preference for at least 3 years in designing high performance, large-scale ML systems 
  * Advanced degree in Computer Science, Data Science, ML or related field, or comparable professional experience 
  * Proficient in Python and ML libraries (e.g., NumPy, SciPy, scikit-learn). 
  * Knowledgeable about various foundational models, such as LLAMA, Mistral and as well as OpenAI APIs & GPT Models 
  * Experience in training models using PyTorch, TensorFlow, Jax 
  * Strong in programming and data querying (SQL, Spark) 
  * Skilled in data wrangling and data manipulation 
  * Expert in handling large, structured, and unstructured datasets, with a special focus on time series, e.g. weather/climate data, satellite imagery, and geospatial data 
  * Demonstrated ability to deploy models at scale in production environments 
  * Proficient in version control (e.g., Git) and cloud computing services (Azure, AWS, GCP) for model training and deployment 

** What you'll enjoy... **

  * Tick destinations off your bucket list with our discounts on travel and accommodation. 
  * Employee Share Scheme through Equate Plus. 
  * Access to in-house financial and health services, and internal 24/7 gym. 
  * Receive ongoing training and professional development through the Flight Centre Landing. 
  * Excellent hybrid working model. 
  * Preference for internal progression through Brightness of Future: Employees have the right to see a clear pathway to achieving career ambitions. 
  * Global career opportunities in a network of brands and businesses at your fingertips. 
  * Proud Corporate Social Responsibility platform through the Flight Centre Foundation, and Brighter Futures programs. 
  * Various social events to promote networking, the celebration of wins, and sometimes just for fun! (Global Gathering 2024 - Portugal). 

** We value you... **

Flight Centre Travel Group is committed to creating an inclusive and diverse
workplace that supports your unique identity to create better, safer
experiences for everyone.​ We encourage you to _ come as you are; _ to foster
inclusivity and collaboration. We celebrate you.

** Who we are... **

Since our beginning, our vision has always been to _ open up the world for
those who want to see. _

As a global travel retailer, our people come from all different backgrounds,
and our connections spread to the far reaches of the globe - 20+ countries and
counting! Together, we are a _ family _ (we call ourselves _ Flighties _ ).

We offer genuine opportunities for people to grow and evolve. We embrace new
experiences, we celebrate the wins, seize all opportunities, and empower all
of our people to find their ** Brightness of Future ** .

We encourage you to ** DREAM BIG ** through collaboration and innovation, and
make sure you are supported to make incredible ideas a reality. Together, we
deliver quality, innovative solutions that delight our customers and achieve
our strategic priorities.

